Types of Waits in Playwright
Implicit Wait
Playwright does not have traditional implicit waits like Selenium.
Instead, it automatically waits for elements to be ready before interacting using locators.
Example: clicking an element waits until it‚Äôs visible and enabled:
page.click("#login")  # auto-waits until the button is ready
. Explicit Wait
You explicitly wait for a specific condition before continuing.
Wait for Selector
page.wait_for_selector("#username")  # waits until element is in DOM and visible


Optional timeout:

page.wait_for_selector("#username", timeout=10000)  # wait up to 10 seconds

b) Wait for Element State
# Wait until element is visible
page.locator("#submit").wait_for(state="visible")
# Wait until element is hidden
page.locator("#spinner").wait_for(state="hidden")
# Other states: "attached", "detached", "visible", "hidden", "enabled", "disabled"
3. Wait for URL / Navigation
Wait until a page navigates to a specific URL:
page.goto("https://example.com/login")
page.wait_for_url("https://example.com/dashboard")  # waits until redirected

Can use regex:
import re
page.wait_for_url(re.compile(r"/dashboard$"))
4. Wait for Load / Network
# Wait until network idle (all requests done)
page.wait_for_load_state("networkidle")
# Other load states:
# "load" -> waits for window.onload
# "domcontentloaded" -> waits for DOMContentLoaded
Example:
page.goto("https://example.com", wait_until="networkidle")
5. Wait for Function / Custom Condition
You can wait for any JS condition:
page.wait_for_function("() => window.myApp && window.myApp.isReady")
Useful for dynamic apps or custom flags.
6. Sleep / Timeout (Not Recommended Usually)
import time
time.sleep(2)  # pauses for 2 seconds
Only use for debugging.
Prefer wait_for_selector or expect, as Playwright smartly waits.
7. Using Expect (Auto-Waiting)
Playwright expect assertions automatically wait:
from playwright.sync_api import expect
expect(page.locator("#welcome")).to_be_visible()  # waits up to default 5s
expect(page.locator("#logout")).to_be_enabled(timeout=10000)  # custom 10s wait
No need to manually add explicit waits most of the time.

